## (1) Brief Project Description

*Devote to creating an exquisite, elegant and simple cloud disk based on the IPFS network and the Filecoin network.*

## (2) Link to Project UI

http://cloud.filevip.top:8089/

## (3) What does your application/UI do?

*document list
File/folder upload + drag and drop upload
File sharing
File monitoring statistics
Recycle bin
Multi-user
WebDav
Scan disk task
Online preview and custom configuration preview engine*

## (4) If your project is using a curated dataset, which one are you using?

*I don’t understand what curated dataset is. We are for Multi-users to upload any data to the IPFS network and Filecoin network.*

## (5) If your project is not using a curated dataset, please tell us a little bit more about your data by answering the questions below.

*What sorts of data will you collect? Do you own or have exclusive rights to the data you plan to use? Is the data license available online? Does the data contain any sensitive or illegal information?*

*What kind of data is collected depends on the user or the company. We will add audit functions in the future, similar to [百度云盘](https://yun.baidu.com/).The review of illegal data in China is very strict. We need to protect users' personal data while ensuring that there is no illegal data.*

## (6) How much data are you planning to store to the Filecoin network during the Slingshot competition?

*Except more than 500TB*

## (7) How are you structuring the data?

*Deduplication and fragmentation technology.*

## (8) What pre-processing are you doing before ingesting the data?

*Analyze and Mirror the data.*

## (9)  What tech stack will you use to store the data?

*We are now using powergate, but we will not give up lotus-API, because personally feel that powergate is much slower than lotus.（need more test)*

## (10) How will you retrieve the data?

*Two copies of data are stored, one is uploaded to filecoin, and the other is saved in Filevip-Cloud-UI. When the user retrieves, the same retrieval request is sent to filecoin, and the other data is directly passed to the user for use. At present, there is only this idea , Has not been implemented yet.*

## (11) Who is the intended user for your application/UI?

*Client and Enterprise.*

## (12) Do you have any users already or plans to acquire users soon?

*Yes. We have found some customers and companies are testing.*

## (13) What challenges do you anticipate with this project?

*1.How to ensure the security of such a huge amount of data;2.Most of the demand is hot data, what should we do;3.How to make trade-offs between compliance and privacy, especially corporate data;*

